&lt;p&gt;Datadog is seeking a highly organized and detailed-oriented Field Marketing Manager who is enthusiastic about event planning, thrives in a demanding environment, and is committed to delivering exceptional client-facing experiences. As a member of the NAMER Field Marketing team, you will be responsible for planning, managing and executing Datadog’s presence at a diverse portfolio of events.You will collaborate with cross-functional teams including Marketing, Sales, Product, Executive, IT, and more to bring our events to life and deliver exceptional, high-impact programs that align with our brand and business objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;At Datadog, we place value in our office culture - the relationships and collaboration it builds, and the creativity it brings to the table. We operate as a hybrid workplace to ensure our Datadogs can create a work-life harmony that best fits them.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute field marketing strategies tailored to the Southeast region, with a strong focus on Mid-Market, Enterprise, and Named account engagement and product adoption&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with regional Sales, Customer Success, and Product Marketing to design programs that align with the buyer journey and product maturity stage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the end-to-end execution of localized events, executive roundtables, user group sessions, and hands-on enablement workshops,hospitality events and more!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build a repeatable marketing playbook that helps move accounts from acquisition to product expansion and advocacy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage tech stack (SFDC, Metabase, Demandbase, Marketo, Tableau) to analyze regional performance, uncover account insights, and optimize campaign effectiveness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Forecast, report on, and manage quarterly budget allocations to support regional pipeline targets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support major Datadog-led events such as DASH, Datadog Summits, Datadog Live, and key industry conferences (e.g., RSA, Google Cloud Next, AWS re:Invent)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a local expert on Southeast trends and customer needs, feeding insights back into campaign development and go-to-market strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2-3 years’ experience in field marketing or event marketing, event management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional attention to detail, strong organizational skills, and a process-driven approach to problem-solving.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactive mindset with the ability to take initiative and anticipate needs, adapting quickly in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to successfully manage multiple tasks and plan and execute multiple events simultaneously while meeting deadlines&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong work ethic, excelling in both self-directed work and collaborative environments, with a consistently positive, team player approach.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience creating and managing marketing content for events (e.g., event collateral, session materials, emails, social posts, landing pages) to drive engagement and support event campaigns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills, with the ability to present ideas thoughtfully and clearly to influence and collaborate effectively across all levels of the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to travel up to 50% of the time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
