&lt;p&gt;We’re hiring an Internal Communications Specialist at our headquarters in New York City to help teams share information across the company as we continue to scale globally. We’re seeking a collaborative and detail-oriented individual with exceptional writing and editing skills, looking to work in a fun, fast-paced, and innovative workplace. As part of the broader People Team, you will make a companywide impact by managing tools, channels, and processes that keep your “packmates” in-the-know, and help to strengthen Datadog’s distinctive company culture.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;At Datadog, we value our office culture, the relationships and collaboration it builds, and the creativity it brings to our teams. We operate as a hybrid workplace to ensure our Datadogs can&amp;nbsp; work-life harmony that best fits them.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead content creation for our internal news channels and intranet, ensuring messages are clear, consistent, and engaging.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with IT, Learning &amp;amp; Development, Benefits, and other teams to craft and distribute communications that reach the right audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the production and execution of our quarterly town hall meetings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Update and oversee our internal platforms, including &lt;em&gt;Bits of Info&lt;/em&gt; (intranet) and digital signage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Moderate companywide email distribution lists to maintain clarity and reduce noise.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, test, and implement new tools and AI applications to improve communications programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coach colleagues on communication best practices and Datadog’s editorial style.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support ad hoc communications projects and campaigns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You want to work for a tech company that’s growing quickly, and where every day feels purposeful.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are an exceptional writer and editor with a sharp eye for detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You measure success through data and analytics to continually improve communication effectiveness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are experienced and/or curious about using new tools and technologies to share news, stories, and information&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have experience working with senior executives, C-suite leaders, or similar&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are organized and possess strong project management and time management skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are a skilled presenter and can represent complex ideas effectively to a variety of audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have a critical eye for visual design; it’s helpful but not required to have experience with graphic design, video editing, or similar.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Also nice but not required: experience with Confluence, Jira, Adobe Creative Suite, Generative AI, and Google Workspace.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Datadog values people from all walks of life. We understand not everyone will meet all the above qualifications on day one. That&#39;s okay. If you’re passionate about technology and want to grow your skills, we encourage you to apply.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
